Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.15,0:00:04.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is not a work of fiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.38,0:00:19.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is a place called "Island of Flowers"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.25,0:00:26.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are in Belém Novo, municipality of Porto Alegre, state of Rio Grande do Sul, in southern Brazil,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.07,0:00:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,more precisely at 30 degrees, 12 minutes and 30 seconds South, and 52 degrees, 11 minutes and 23 seconds West.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.58,0:00:40.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are currently walking in a tomato plantation, and we can see ahead, standing, a human being, in this case, a japanese man.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.96,0:00:47.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The japanese are distinguished from other human beings by the shape of their eyes, their black hair, and by their characteristic names. 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.51,0:00:49.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The japanese man in question is called
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.65,0:00:51.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suzuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.84,0:00:56.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Human beings are biped mammals, and distinguish themselves from other mammals, like whales,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.39,0:01:03.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or bipeds, like chickens, mainly by two characteristics: a highly developed telencephalon, and opposable thumbs.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.81,0:01:09.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The highly developed telencephalon allows human beings to store, associate, process and understand pieces of information.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.51,0:01:17.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The opposable thumb allows human beings a tweezer-like finger movement, which in turn allows for precise manipulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.23,0:01:23.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The highly developed telencephalon combined with the tweezer-like finger movement allowed human beings
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.48,0:01:28.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to make innumerable improvements to their planet, including
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.76,0:01:31.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,growing tomatoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.42,0:01:34.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomatoes, unlike whales, chickens, and japanese people
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.15,0:01:36.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is a vegetable.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.15,0:01:41.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fruit of the tomato plant, tomatoes started being cultivated in the 1800s for its nutritional qualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.25,0:01:45.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Around 61 million tons of tomatoes are produces on Earth every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.15,0:01:51.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr Suzuki, despite working almost 12 hours daily, is responsible for a very small fraction of this production.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.90,0:01:56.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The main use of tomatoes is the feeding of humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.92,0:02:03.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Suzuki is a japanese man, and, therefore, a human being.  Despite this, Mr. Suzuki does not grow tomatoes with the intention to eat them. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.24,0:02:08.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Almost all tomatoes grown by Mr. Suzuki are delivered to the supermarket in exchange for money.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.91,0:02:16.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Money was most likely created as an initiative by Giges, King of Lidia, a great kingdom in Asia Minor, in the 7th centure before Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.98,0:02:19.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Christ was a jew.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.91,0:02:24.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jews have a highly developed telencephalon  and opposable thumbs.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.40,0:02:28.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are, therefore, human beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.52,0:02:32.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until the creation of money, the economy was based on the direct exchange of goods.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.16,0:02:35.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The difficulty of calculating the amount of tomatoes equivalent to a chicken
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.56,0:02:41.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the difficulty of the direct exchange of chickens for whales where the main motivations for the creation of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.51,0:02:45.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Starting in the thrid centure BC, any action of object made by human beings
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.68,0:02:50.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,fruit of the collaboration between the highly developed telencephalon  and the opposable thumbs, 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.68,0:02:57.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as well as all living things, above and below ground -- tomatoes, chickens and whales -- can be exchanged for money.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.80,0:03:02.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To facilitate the exchange of tomatoes for money, human beings created supermarkets.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.15,0:03:07.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Anete is a Roman Apostolic Catholic biped mammal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.47,0:03:13.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She has a highly developed telencephalon and opposable thumbs.  She is, therefore, a human being.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.59,0:03:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She came to this supermarket in order to exchange her money for tomatoes, amongst other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.00,0:03:23.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Anete obtained her money in exchange for the work she performs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.72,0:03:29.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She uses her highly developed telencephalon and opposable thumbs to exchange perfumes for money.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.47,0:03:36.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perfumes are liquids usually extracted from flowers, which make human beings smell more pleasantly than they would naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.56,0:03:42.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Anete does not extract the perfumes. She exchanges them, at a factory, for a determined amount of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.98,0:03:49.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once that is done, Ms. Anete walks from house to house, exchanging the perfumes for a slightly larger amount of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.84,0:03:52.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The difference between these two amount is called
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.49,0:03:54.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,profit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.24,0:03:58.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Profit, which was once forbidden to Catholics, is today allowed for all human beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.79,0:04:07.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Anete's profit is small compared to the factory's profit, but it is enough to be exchanged for 1kg of tomatoes and 2 kg of meat -- in this case, the meat of a pig.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.84,0:04:12.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pigs are mammals, like humans and whales, but quadrupeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.65,0:04:18.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They sever as food for the Japanese, the Catholics, and the remaining human beings -- with exception of the Jews.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.14,0:04:25.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The food that Ms. Anete exchanged for money, which she exchanged for perfumes extracted from flowers, will be consumed by her family during a single day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.66,0:04:30.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A day is the time interval that it takes for the Earth to spin all the way around it's own axis.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.92,0:04:34.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mid-day is lunch time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.43,0:04:43.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A family is a community formed by a man and a woman, united in matrimony, and by the children born out of this union.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.22,0:04:48.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some of the tomatoes Mr. Suzuki exchanged with the supermarket for money, and which were in turn exchanged for the money 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.49,0:04:54.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that Ms. Anete obtained as profit in the exchange of perfumes extracted from flowers were transformed into sauce for the pork.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.84,0:05:01.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One of these tomatoes, which according to Ms. Anete was in no condition to become sauce, was thrown in the garbage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.95,0:05:09.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Garbage is all that is produced by human beings, in a collaboration between the highly developed telencephalon and the opposable thumbs
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.10,0:05:13.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and that, according to the opinion of some human being, is in no condition to become sauce.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.91,0:05:19.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In a city like Porto Alegre, inhabited by over a million human beings, produces around 500 tons of garbage daily.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.84,0:05:24.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Garbage attracts all kinds of germs and bacteria, which in turn cause disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.12,0:05:27.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Diseases seriously harm the normal functioning of human beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.95,0:05:32.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even when it does cause disease, the apearence and aroma of garbage are extremely unpleasant.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.63,0:05:41.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is why garbage is taken a determined places, very far, where it can freely soil, smell badly and attract disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.81,0:05:46.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In Porto Alegre, one of the places chosen for garbage to smell badly and attract disease is called
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.00,0:05:51.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Island of Flowers
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.92,0:05:56.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An island is a portion of land surrounded by water from all sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.62,0:06:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Water is a odorless, insipid and discoloured substance, formed by two hydrogen atoms and one oxygen atom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.14,0:06:08.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Flowers are the reproductive organs of plants, usually scented and with bright colours.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.77,0:06:15.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pleasantly smelling flowers can be turned into perfume, like the ones Ms Anete exchanged for money, which she in turn exchanged for tomatoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.09,0:06:19.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are few flower at the Island of Flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.14,0:06:25.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is, however, a lot of garbage, and amongst it, the tomato Ms. Anete judged inadequate for the pork sauce.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.25,0:06:29.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is also a lot of pigs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.24,0:06:34.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The tomato Ms Anete judged inadequate for the pork she was serving as food for her family
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.50,0:06:39.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,, may turn out to be a great meal for a pig and its family, in the opinion of th epig.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.64,0:06:46.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is important to remember Ms Anete has a highly developed telencephalon  and opposable thumbs, while pigs don't even have thumbs, let alone opposable ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.98,0:06:51.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pigs have, however, an owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.27,0:06:57.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A pig's owner is a human being, with a highly developed telencephalon, opposable thumbs and money.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.07,0:07:04.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The pig's owner exchanged a small part of his money for a small plot of land in the Island of Flowers, thus becoming the owner of the plot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.04,0:07:08.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A plot of land is a patch of land which has an owner and a fence.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.04,0:07:14.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This plot, where garbage is thrown, was fenced so that the pigs would not be able to go out, and so that human beings would not come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.00,0:07:25.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The employees of the pig's owner separate the organic matter which they think is fit for the pig's consumption from the garbage.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.83,0:07:29.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Organic matter is anything that was once living, in either animal or vegetable form.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.85,0:07:33.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomates, chickens, pigs, flowers and paper are all organic matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.35,0:07:42.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This piece of paper, for example, was used on a history test for high school students at the Nossa Senhora de Dores school,  and was given to the student Ana Luiza Nunes, a human being.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.34,0:07:48.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A history test is a test for the capacity of a human being's telencephalon  to remember data related to the study of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.42,0:07:52.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For example: who as Mem de Sá? What were the hereditary captaincies?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.31,0:07:55.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To remember is to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.43,0:08:01.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some organic materials, like tomatoes and history tests, are given to pigs as food.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.64,0:08:07.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That which they consider inapropriate for the feeding of pigs, is used to feed women and children.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.46,0:08:17.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Women and children are human beings, with a highly developed telencephalon, opposable thumbs and no money.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.19,0:08:23.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They don't have an owner, and what is worse, they are many.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.69,0:08:31.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Being many, they are organized by the employees of the pig's owner into groups of 10, and they have the permission to go inside the fenced area.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.12,0:08:42.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once inside the fenced area they can choose for themselves all the food the employees of the pig's owner judged innadequate for the pigs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.72,0:08:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The employees stipulated that each group of 10 human beings has 5 minutes to stay within the fenced area
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.20,0:08:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,collecting organic matter, like tomatoes and history tests.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.75,0:09:00.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,5 minutes are 300 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.55,0:09:11.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since 1958, the second was defined as the equivalent of 9 billion, 192 million, 631 thousand and 770 cycles of radiation from a Cesium atom.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.52,0:09:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cesium is a non-organic material found in the garbage in Goiânia.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.03,0:09:26.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The tomato, planted by Mr. Suzuki, exchanged for money at the supermarket,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.03,0:09:33.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,exchanged for the money that Ms Anete exchanged for perfumes extracted from flowers, rejected for the pork sauce, thrown in the garbage,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.84,0:09:38.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,rejected as food by the pigs, is now available for all the human beings at Island of Flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.75,0:09:49.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What places the human beings at the Island of Flowers after the pigs in the priority for food choice
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.26,0:09:53.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is the fact they have no money.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.72,0:10:09.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Human beings distinguish themselves from other animals by the highly developed telencephalon, opposable thumbs, and by being free.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.63,0:10:14.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Free is the state of a person with freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.32,0:10:19.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Freedom is a word fed by human dreams, 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.03,0:10:21.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that no one can explain,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.42,0:10:24.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and that nobody cannot understand.
